/**
@var FOOD
See @ref page_type_6
*/

/**
@page page_type_6 Food

            By eating/drinking food-objects, the player can fill his
            stomach and gain a little health. 



Type defined by:
- @ref object::type = 6


# Attributes

<table>
	<tr>
		<th>Attribute</th>
		<th>Field</th>
		<th>Description</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>AC modifier</td>
		<td>@ref living::ac</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will result in this amount
                being added to the player's AC until the food effect wears off.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>WC modifier</td>
		<td>@ref living::wc</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will result in this amount
                being added to the player's WC until the food effect wears off.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>artifact</td>
		<td>@ref object::artifact</td>
		<td>            If defined, refers to an artifact to get values from.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>attack type</td>
		<td>@ref object::attacktype</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will grant the
                player the set attacktypes.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>attuned paths</td>
		<td>@ref object::path_attuned</td>
		<td>                Click on the &lt;attuned paths&gt; button to select spellpaths.
                If set on a food with a non-null title, the player will get attuned to
                the specified spellpaths for the duration of the food effect.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>blinding</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_BLIND</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will blind the player until
                the food effect wears off.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>block view</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_BLOCKSVIEW</td>
		<td>            If an item is set to block view, players (and monsters) cannot see
            beyond it unless they cross it or manage to stand on top.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>blocks prayers</td>
		<td>@ref page_custom_attribute_blocks_prayer "blocks_prayer"</td>
		<td>            Similar to damned, but does not appear in detect curse.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>changing</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_CHANGING</td>
		<td>            A &lt;changing&gt; object converts to &lt;food&gt; &lt;other_arch&gt;
            objects; when it's animation is done. For non-living objects &lt;food&gt;
            is checked: if it is zero, the change happens; otherwise &lt;food&gt;
            is decreased by one. I suggest you don't mess with this value -
            leave the default in place.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>charisma</td>
		<td>@ref living::Cha</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will result in this amount
                being added to the player's charisma until the food effect wears off.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>client-sided randomized animation?</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_CLIENT_ANIM_RANDOM</td>
		<td>            If defined, then the object's animation is client-sided. Similar
            objects are animated independently.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>client-sided synchronized animation?</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_CLIENT_ANIM_SYNC</td>
		<td>            If defined, then the object's animation is client-sided. Similar
            objects are animated synchronized.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>constitution</td>
		<td>@ref living::Con</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will result in this amount
                being added to the player's constitution until the food effect wears off.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>denied paths</td>
		<td>@ref object::path_denied</td>
		<td>                Click on the &lt;denied paths&gt; button to select spellpaths.
                If set on a food with a non-null title, the player will be denied
                the specified spellpaths for the duration of the food effect.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>dexterity</td>
		<td>@ref living::Dex</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will result in this amount
                being added to the player's dexterity until the food effect wears off.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>elevation</td>
		<td>@ref page_custom_attribute_elevation "elevation"</td>
		<td>            The elevation (height above sea level) of this square. It is used
            for weather calculations and should be in the range -32000..32000.
            The elevation of a tile must be set in the bottom-most game object;
            elevation values for non-bottom-most game objects are ignored by the
            Crossfire server.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>food points</td>
		<td>@ref living::food</td>
		<td>            The player's stomach will get filled with this amount of food
            points. The player's health will increase by &lt;food points&gt;/50
            hp. If title or artifact is set, a force effect is inserted into
            the player's inventory that grants boosts from sections effects and
            resistances for &lt;food points&gt;/4 seconds.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>garbage generated when eaten</td>
		<td>@ref page_custom_attribute_on_use_yield "on_use_yield"</td>
		<td>            If set to an archetype, this archetype will replace the eaten item.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>glow radius</td>
		<td>@ref object::glow_radius</td>
		<td>            If &lt;glow radius&gt; is set to a value greater zero, the object
            appears lit up on dark maps. &lt;glow radius&gt; can be a value
            between 0 and 4, the higher, the more light does the object emit.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>godgiven item</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_STARTEQUIP</td>
		<td>            A godgiven item vanishes as soon as the player drops it to the
            ground.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>grace regeneration</td>
		<td>@ref living::maxgrace</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will grant the player
                an adjustment to their grace regeneration rate equal to &lt;grace regeneration&gt;.
                Negative values slow regeneration, positive values increase it.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>health regeneration</td>
		<td>@ref living::maxhp</td>
		<td>                If set on a food with a non-null title, consumption will grant the player
                an adjustment to their hitpoint regeneration rate equal to &lt;health regeneration&gt;.
                Negative values slow regeneration, positive values increase it.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>health restored</td>
		<td>@ref living::hp</td>
		<td>                At the time of eating, this food will restore an additional &lt;health restored&gt;
                hit points, in addition to the basic healing tied to the &lt;food&gt; value.
                Negative values drain health instead of restore it.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>identified</td>
		<td>@ref FLAG_IDENTIFIED</td>
		<td>            If an item is identified, the player has full knowledge about it.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>identified animation</td>
		<td>@ref page_custom_attribute_identified_animation "identified_animation"</td>
		<td>            If defined, then the object will take this animation when
            identified.
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>identified animation speed</td>
		<td>@ref page_custom_attribute_identified_anim_speed "identified_anim_speed"</td>
		<td>            If defined, then the object will have this animation speed when
